        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 16 at 3:22PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 322 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Horatio, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
De Queen, Horatio, West Otis, Cerrogordo, West Line and Shinewell.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
